text: Transavia is a Dutch and French low-cost carrier. It is currently owned by Air France-KLM. It began on January 3, 1966. It was the third airline founded in the Netherlands. The first scheduled flight happened on October 26, 1986. It has scheduled (planned) and charter (irregular) flights to many destinations in Europe. ==Gallery== File:PHTVH (6790687071).jpg|A Transavia airplane at Gatwick Airport File:PH-HZM B737-8K2-W Transavia LPA 31JAN09 (3242792060).jpg|A Transavia Boeing 737 File:Transavia office Schiphol.jpg|Transavia headquarters ==References== Category:Low-cost airlines Category:1966 establishments in Europe Category:1960s establishments in the Netherlands Category:1960s establishments in France Category:Airlines of France
